<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10010737>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Fine scale vegetation and land use patterns in Tucumán province, showing collecting localities. A: Sampling sites; B: Courses and bodies of water, C: Semi-arid Chaco ecorregion; D: Las Yungas ecorregion; E: Transitions zones and climate transformed Cw; F: Dry haze grassland; G: La Puna; H: Urban areas; I: Altoandino; J: Forest in gallery; K: Bare ground; L: Departments of Tucumán. Yungas and Bosque Chaqueño, as used here are subsets of “tropical and subtropical moist forest”, and “tropical and subtropical dry broadleaf forest”, respectively, of Olson et al. (2001). Modified from Brown & Pacheco (2005)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10010737/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

